        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In a multi index search, id are change with :\r\n{code} \r\nif ($indexShift != 0) {\r\n      foreach ($hits as $hit) {\r\n            $hit->id += $indexShift;\r\n      }\r\n}{code}\r\n\r\nbut id must be document id, so when i use\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nforeach($hits as $hit) {\r\n        $document = $hit->getDocument();\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nthere are an error.\r\n\r\nSo, to fix that, i have submitted a PR with update unit test to cover this case.\r\nIn Query\\Hit, id is a unique hit (no based on id document) and document_id is the doc id.\r\nSo, no confusion and multi search run good."
        },
